The paper is about a model for social network formation, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the efficiency and stability of the networks, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The use of directed edges and short paths suggests a focus on network analysis (cs.SI) and the use of asynchronous dynamics suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
